<subSubSection id="C7D06578FFE8E020FF2458F2F8A6FD10" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" type="description">
<paragraph id="8F7536F3FFE8E020FF2458F2FF6DFD6E" blockId="1.[174,1233,452,768]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
Salticid species 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FE6058F2F952FE30" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[423,553,452,479]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantulus">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FE6058F2F952FE30" box="[423,553,452,479]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. tantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a Trans-Palearctic temperate range; from 
<collectingCountry id="F7DD7663FFE8E020FBBE58F2FFB7FE0E" box="[1145,1228,453,480]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">France</collectingCountry>
, through C. Europe, the middle Urals and C. Siberia, east to Magadan Area, south to Tuva and C. 
<collectingCountry id="F7DD7663FFE8E020FF395B32FA0BFDCE" box="[254,368,517,544]" name="Mongolia" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EB5B4B02FFE8E020FEBA5B32F949FDCE" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[381,562,517,544]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" pagination="221 - 286" refId="ref1451" refString="Logunov, D. V. A redefinition of the genera Bianor Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1885 and Harmochirus Simon, 1885, with the establishment of a new genus Sibianor gen. n. (Aranei: Salticidae) // Arthropoda Selecta. - 2000. - N 4. - P. 221 - 286." type="journal article" year="2000">Logunov, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In N. Osetiya 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FD185B32F822FDF0" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[735,857,516,543]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantulus">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FD185B32F822FDF0" box="[735,857,516,543]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. tantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens habitats are in steppe and young oak forests and steppe meadows (
<bibRefCitation id="EB5B4B02FFE8E020FD775B12F81EFDAE" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[688,869,549,576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" pagination="221 - 286" refId="ref1451" refString="Logunov, D. V. A redefinition of the genera Bianor Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1885 and Harmochirus Simon, 1885, with the establishment of a new genus Sibianor gen. n. (Aranei: Salticidae) // Arthropoda Selecta. - 2000. - N 4. - P. 221 - 286." type="journal article" year="2000">Logunov, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Our specimens were collected in dry birch forest with meadow grasses. As in case of 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FCE05B72F807FDB0" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2000" box="[807,892,580,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larae">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FCE05B72F807FDB0" box="[807,892,580,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. larae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FBFC5B72FFCDFDB0" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1083,1206,580,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantulus">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FBFC5B72FFCDFDB0" box="[1083,1206,580,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. tantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very wide but its finds in Palearctic are small in numbers (
<bibRefCitation id="EB5B4B02FFE8E020FC935B52FF71FD6E" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[852,1034,613,640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" pagination="221 - 286" refId="ref1451" refString="Logunov, D. V. A redefinition of the genera Bianor Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1885 and Harmochirus Simon, 1885, with the establishment of a new genus Sibianor gen. n. (Aranei: Salticidae) // Arthropoda Selecta. - 2000. - N 4. - P. 221 - 286." type="journal article" year="2000">Logunov, 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F7536F3FFE8E020FF245BB2F8A6FD10" blockId="1.[174,1233,452,768]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
In the fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="F7DD7663FFE8E020FE485BB2FA94FD4E" box="[399,495,645,672]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FE325BB2F932FD70" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2000" box="[501,585,644,671]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larae">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FE325BB2F932FD70" box="[501,585,644,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. larae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FDB85BB2F982FD70" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[639,761,644,671]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantulus">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FDB85BB2F982FD70" box="[639,761,644,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. tantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized as very rare species, therefore further research is needed for their finding and protection. I support Joost Vogels’ (2012) recommendation for arachnologists to verify their own and/or museum collections for clarification of 
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FE4F5BD2F9F4FD10" box="[392,655,740,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FE4F5BD2F955FD10" baseAuthorityName="Ohlert" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[392,558,741,767]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurocinctus">S. aurocinctus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FDFF5BD2F9F4FD10" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2000" box="[568,655,740,767]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larae">S. larae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="48CA4D70FFE8E020FD0F5BD2F838FD10" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[712,835,740,767]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sibianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantulus">
<emphasis id="BDBEEAE1FFE8E020FD0F5BD2F838FD10" box="[712,835,740,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">S. tantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distribution.
</paragraph>
